04/03/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- The power utility KESH sacked chief Andi Beli on Friday (March 2nd), at the request of Prime Minister Sali Berisha, who accused Beli of mismanagement. A severe energy crisis hit the country in December, forcing daily power cuts lasting 18 hours in some areas. Deputy Energy Minister Gjergji Bojaxhi was tapped to replace Beli. (Albanian News, Focus - 03/03/07)
